highcharter.Rmd

Highcharts

let us start start with a simple example using hchart function.

library(highcharter)

# install.packages("palmerpenguins")
data(penguins, package = "palmerpenguins") 

hchart(
  penguins,
  "scatter",
  hcaes(x = flipper_length_mm, y = bill_length_mm, group = species)
)

Among its features {highcharter} can chart various objects depending of its class with the generic hchart function.

x <- c(rnorm(10000), rnorm(1000, 4, 0.5))

hchart(x, name = "data")

One of the nicest class which hchart can plot is the forecast class from the {forecast} package.

library(forecast)

airforecast <- forecast(auto.arima(AirPassengers), level = 95)

hchart(airforecast)
